Scenario: The adoption walkthrough's terminal section names the three observable end-state moves an adopter must achieve (lead-shop container, per-BC containers registered, first dispatch)
  Given the shopsystem-docs repository contains an adoption walkthrough (one or more linked markdown files) starting from the entry document
  When the walkthrough's markdown is parsed for the named end-state section (the final section the walkthrough designates as completion)
  Then the section names, as an executable step, the move that brings a lead-shop container up on the adopter's host
  And the section names, as an executable step, the move that registers each BC the adopter's manifest declares with the messaging registry such that "shop-msg registry list" reports both the lead and each BC by name
  And the section names, as an executable step, the move that dispatches an assign_scenarios message from a Claude Code session opened against the lead-shop container to one of the adopter's BCs
  And the section states explicitly that successful completion of these three moves is what "the framework is bootstrapped" means in v1
